    <question number="2">
        <prompt>How did joint-stock companies demonstrate early capitalism?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">They were government-owned</option>
            <option letter="b">They allowed shared investment and risk</option>
            <option letter="c">They prohibited private ownership</option>
            <option letter="d">They operated as charities</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>Joint-stock companies demonstrated capitalist principles by allowing multiple investors to share both risks and potential profits.</explanation>
